The paper deals with the recovery of points on a smooth surface in high-dimensional space, with application to dynamic imaging. This suggests that the paper could belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The paper also relies on nuclear norm minimization and iterative algorithms, which are commonly used in numerical analysis (cs.NA) and information theory (cs.IT). The use of the algorithm in recovering free breathing and ungated cardiac data suggests that the paper could also belong to the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG) and signal processing (cs.SI).
